I had a slight problem after upgrading from Parallels 4 to 5:  My Windows XP SP3 Bootcamp partition would not boot up.  It would only go to a Blue Screen of Death noting that I had encountered a "IRQL_NOT_LESS_OR_EQUAL" error.

After digging up the official fix for the problem at the Parallels website (link below), I followed their instructions and all was fixed.  You just need to start your virtual machine using a single processor the first time, let it install the new Tools data, then you can revert back to your normal setting for every subsequent boot.

Details:
http://kb.parallels.com/en/6873
Thanks Apokarteron, its a keeper!

ALBINOZ - See my comment above.  I had the same problem, and was about to my wits' end before I thought to Google the exact phrase of the BSoD error along with 'Parallels 5'.

The link above to the Parallels knowledge base article SOLVES this problem conclusively.  Also, the basic instructions are insluded in my post.

For reference, my testing machine was an eight-core 2.8GHz Mac Pro desktop, running OS 10.6.2.

After starting the first time using only one processor, and installing the Parallels Tools onto the Bootcamp partition, I was able to quit Parallels, and restart it after changing the configuration back to the full 8 processors without the BSoD appearing.

Everything works flawlessly now.

Hey guys jst dled and got everything to work

1. Turn off airport after downloading.
2. Install. (leave airport off)
3. Restart when prompted. (airport still off)
4. After restart, start parallels. (airport still off)
5. Click Activate. (airport still off)
6. Enter serial from Serial.rtf. (airport still off)
7. Don't Register. (airport still off)
8. Turn airport back on.

Worked for me hope it works for you!
